Drop -Werror from cet_set_compiler_flags and guard the test subdir.

Two tests-off / GCC-14-C++20 fixes for the conda build:
1. larcore builds DIAGS CAUTIOUS + WERROR; under GCC 14 / C++20 (our art-stack
   standard, vs upstream's C++17 default) the stricter diagnostics get promoted to
   hard errors. CXXFLAGS can't demote cetmodules' add_compile_options(-Werror), so
   drop the WERROR keyword. See conda/potential_improvements.md (#2).
2. test/Geometry/CMakeLists.txt calls cet_test_env() referencing
   ${larcorealg_BINARY_DIR} (a source-tree path that does not exist when larcorealg
   is an installed package rather than an in-tree subdirectory). With
   -DBUILD_TESTING=OFF (the packaging default) the tests are not built anyway, so
   only descend into test/ when BUILD_TESTING is ON.
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -17,7 +17,6 @@
 cet_cmake_env()

 cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS CAUTIOUS
-  WERROR
   NO_UNDEFINED
   EXTRA_FLAGS -pedantic -Wno-unused-local-typedefs
 )
@@ -43,7 +42,9 @@
 add_subdirectory(larcore)

 # tests
-add_subdirectory(test)
+if(BUILD_TESTING)
+  add_subdirectory(test)
+endif()

 # ups - table and config files
